<h1 id="13-minimalis-conky">13. <a href="https://www.gnome-look.org/p/1112273/">Minimalis Conky</a></h1>
<p>This is an elegant-looking Conky. I thought it was not possible to find a Conky theme that was minimalist and beautiful at the same time. But this Conky proved that I was completely wrong. Many of you, including me, want this type of Conky, which does not take up much space on the desktop, instead of showing all the useful parameters in easily readable text.</p>

<p><img src="/assets/img/conky/minimalis-1.jpg" alt="Minimalis Conky" /></p>

<p><a href="https://www.gnome-look.org/p/1112273/" class="btn btn-success btn-lg" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"> Get Minimalis Conky </a></p>

<hr />

<h1 id="14-equalizer-conky">14. <a href="https://www.gnome-look.org/p/1112402/">Equalizer Conky</a></h1>
<p>Do not get confused with the name. Because this theme will not display the equalizer on your media player or allow you to adjust the ups and downs of the music that is playing. Instead, it will display common system status parameters with a few vertical bars that look exactly like an equalizer view.</p>

<p><img src="/assets/img/conky/equalizer-conky.jpg" alt="Conky Equalizer" /></p>

<p><a href="https://www.gnome-look.org/p/1112402/" class="btn btn-success btn-lg" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"> Get the Equalizer Conky </a></p>

<hr />

<h1 id="15-infinity-dark">15. <a href="https://www.gnome-look.org/p/1006547/">Infinity Dark</a></h1>
<p>Infinity Dark is a beautiful Conky that prioritizes the time and date. The developer included the Monofur font face with this theme, which makes the date and time even more vibrant. This theme uses the Entypo icon set to view disk usage, network activity, etc. It also shows CPU load, RAM usage and system uptime.</p>

<p><img src="/assets/img/conky/infinite-dark-1.jpg" alt="Dark infinity" /></p>

